WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.270 --> 00:00:06.630
- I've found that not only
giving a bunch of context

2
00:00:06.630 --> 00:00:07.860
at the beginning is really helpful,

3
00:00:07.860 --> 00:00:10.477
but I always like to add, at the end,

4
00:00:10.477 --> 00:00:13.110
"Please ask me any follow-up
or clarifying questions

5
00:00:13.110 --> 00:00:15.420
before you continue doing work."

6
00:00:15.420 --> 00:00:16.830
And that has been really helpful,

7
00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:20.670
because when it's coming
up with an end-to-end plan

8
00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:22.270
for whatever task I've given it,

9
00:00:23.490 --> 00:00:24.577
if it pauses and says,

10
00:00:24.577 --> 00:00:27.300
"Okay, well, actually what
about this task do I not know

11
00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:29.670
and I need to ask me, the user?"

12
00:00:29.670 --> 00:00:31.860
I can then answer those proactively

13
00:00:31.860 --> 00:00:34.290
and make sure the output is
something that I'm happy with,

14
00:00:34.290 --> 00:00:37.230
rather than, you know,
Gemini does a bunch of work,

15
00:00:37.230 --> 00:00:39.930
and then I review it, and then
I'm not super happy with it,

16
00:00:39.930 --> 00:00:41.280
and we have keep iterating.